 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   c &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $$a = \cos 5\theta ,\,b = i\sin 5\theta  = c,\,d = \cos 5\theta $$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $${a^2} - {b^2} = {\cos ^2}5\theta  + {\sin ^2}5\theta  = 1$$<br><br>$${a^2} - {c^2} = {\cos ^2}5\theta  + {\sin ^2}5\theta  = 1$$<br><br>$${a^2} - {d^2} = {\cos ^2}5\theta  - {\cos ^2}5\theta  = 1$$<br><br>$${a^2} + {b^2} = {\cos ^2}5\theta  - {\sin ^2}5\theta  = \cos 10\theta  = \cos {{10\pi } \over {24}}$$<br><br>and $$0 &lt; \cos {{5\pi } \over {12}} &lt; 1 $$
<br><br>$$\Rightarrow 0 \le {a^2} + {b^2} \le 1$$
